  "doc_id": "21676",
  "text": "Mechanisms of effects of mutations on ENaC cell surface density. In epithelial cells, ENaC subunits are synthesized in the endoplasmic reticulum and transported specifically to the apical membrane facing the lumen. The route of transport of the subunits apparently proceeds via the Golgi complex and the trans-Golgi network. The proteins are then probably packaged in vesicular endosomes that are directed to the apical membrane [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Studies on a variety of apical proteins have revealed several alternative routes of vesicular trafficking [CITATION_3] . In some cell types, ENaC appear to be transported in membrane lipid raft domains [CITATION_4] .",
